regression_budget: 15ms
agent_goal: Detect async Rust code that holds a std::sync or parking_lot Mutex/RwLock guard across .await, then scope or drop the guard before the await or move the state boundary to tokio::sync.
reference_repositories: tokio-rs/tokio,hyperium/hyper,tower-rs/tower
reference_patterns: Tokio exposes async-aware synchronization primitives when a guard must interact with async scheduling. | Runtime-facing code keeps synchronous Mutex and RwLock critical sections short and outside suspension points.
target_rationale: The fixture is a tiny async boundary check; validating the lock-scope pattern should remain bounded in unit-test scale.
